                <head>297. Telegram 931 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d297fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/10–1855. Secret; Priority.
                        Drafted by Sebald.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1955-10-19">October 19, 1955, 4:09 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d297-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d297-1"/>
                <p>931. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>. Deptel 914.</p>
                <p>Second sentence para 5 should follow first sentence para 4.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
